1

Tuesday, January 1, 1952

Worked all day (except for listening to Rose Bowl game; also a visit to Mc Clellans) on Crotalus unicolor. Made good progress, but there is more to be done on it that I had expected.

Notes:

Awramj

Tuesday, January 1, 1952

5

Saturday, January 5, 1952

Worked all day putting the finishing touches on the South American paper and think it is now really finished.

Symphony concert in the evening.

Notes:

Awramj

Saturday, January 5, 1952

Page Edit History:
  • Awramj 09/17/2012 08:47 PM

6

Sunday, January 6, 1952

Spent part of the morning getting out rattler pictures for Davis of the California Academy of Sciences, who will be down next week.

Then spent the rest of the day packing specimens for return to their owners.

Notes:

Awramj

Sunday, January 6, 1952

12

Saturday, January 12, 1952

Miscellaneous work in the morning. Read the South American paper once more. In the afternoon had a meeting with Benjamin Draper of CAS about a profile for Pacific Discovery, their magazine. Then went over the Bulletin of the Antivenin Institute of America and found some new snake bite material for (Section) 13.

Notes:

Awramj

Saturday, January 12, 1952

Page Edit History:
  • Awramj 09/17/2012 09:02 PM
  • BPOC 09/17/2012 05:38 PM

13

Sunday, January 13, 1952

Spent the Entire day packing rattlesnakes for return to their owners. Got them packed but there is still labeling of the packages to do. A hard, long job, now practically finished.

Notes:

Awramj

Sunday, January 13, 1952

Saturday, January 19, 1952

Back bothering me. Finished going through the Bulletin of the Antivenin Institute in search of snake bite items. Got a number of them.

Awramj

Sunday, January 20, 1952

Back still bad. With Hunter's help got the rattlers all packed and ready for return to their owners. Otherwise nothing accomplished except miscellaneous filing.

Notes:

Awramj

23

Wednesday, January 23, 1952

Went to Los Angeles on the 11:45 AM train. Attended a meeting of the board of directors of Founders Insurance Co from 3 to 4. Spent the time from 4:15 to 6:15 at the LA Public Library and cleared up a few items.
Caught the Lark for San Francisco.

Notes:

Awramj

Wednesday, January 23, 1952

Page Edit History:
  • Awramj 09/17/2012 09:11 PM
  • BPOC 09/17/2012 05:38 PM

24

Thursday, January 24, 1952

Went to Chickering and Gregory's Office from 9:15 to 9:45; then to a meeting of the Light & Power Council. Back to C & G at 2:15; stayed until nearly 4. Then went out to the Academy from 5 to 5:45. Stayed at Wormser's.

Notes:

Awramj

Thursday, January 24, 1952

Page Edit History:
  • Awramj 09/17/2012 09:14 PM
  • BPOC 09/17/2012 05:38 PM

25

Friday, January 25, 1952

Spent the day at MVZ and the UC Library at Berkeley. At MVZ from 10:30 to 11:30. Saw Stebbins and others. At the Library, Biol., Bancroft, and Main, from 11:30 to 6:30. Then caught the Lark.

Notes:

Awramj

Friday, January 25, 1952

Page Edit History:
  • Awramj 09/17/2012 09:17 PM
  • BPOC 09/17/2012 05:38 PM

26

Saturday, January 26, 1952

The Lark was 1 hr. & 10 min late. Went to the Zoo directors meeting, and spent the rest of the afternoon ineffectually trying to catch up.

Notes:

Awramj

Saturday, January 26, 1952

Page Edit History:
  • Awramj 09/17/2012 09:19 PM

Sunday, January 27, 1952

Spent the day catching up and getting ready for the eastern trip. Worked hard and long.

Notes:

Awramj

Awramj

32

Friday, February 1, 1952

Arrived in Chicago at 10:30 AM. Got a good hotel room but had to wait an hour for the baggage to come up.

Talked to Uhle and Lynch from 1 to 2:30.

Worked at the Newberry Library from 2:45 to 6. Picked up the data on the Hernan Gallegos ms. and several other items.

Had dinner with the Lynches.

Page Edit History:
  • Awramj 09/29/2012 12:08 AM
  • BPOC 09/17/2012 05:38 PM

33

Went to the Chicago Natural History Museum at 9:15. Had a long talk with Schmidt about the Chuck List, my book and other herpetological matters. Looked at rattler specimens and had lunch with Schmidt.

Worked at the John Crerar Library from 2 to 4:30. Ran down a few items but in general progress was poor.

Had dinner with the Uhle's.

Page Edit History:
  • Awramj 09/29/2012 12:11 AM
  • BPOC 09/17/2012 05:38 PM

34

Sunday, February 3, 1952

Went to the Chicago Academy of Sciences at 9:10 and worked until 11:20 when Gloyd came in. Talked things over and went to lunch at a new place across the street. Then worked for 50 minutes more and finished everything I wanted to see except 3 of Burger's Venezuelan specimens. Went back to the Palmer House at 1:45 and caught the Century for N.Y. at 4:30. Had a talk with Bob Heyneman.

Page Edit History:
  • Awramj 09/29/2012 12:15 AM
  • BPOC 09/17/2012 05:38 PM

35

Monday, February 4, 1952

Arrived in N.Y. at 9:30 AM. Saw Bogert from 11:30 to 3:30. Specimens and AMNH library. Then worked from 4 to 5:30 at the NY Public Library mostly finding what was available in the catalogue. Went to Guys and Dolls in the evening.

Page Edit History:
  • Awramj 09/29/2012 12:18 AM
  • BPOC 09/17/2012 05:38 PM

36

Tuesday, February 5, 1952

Worked at the AMNH Library from 9:15 to 11. Then went with Bogert to the Bronx Zoo and met Oliver. Had lunch with the Zoo group and met a lot of people. Talked over the proposed venom project with Oliver and Goss the veterinarian. Met Bridges, TeeVan, Knobloch, Atz, Coats, Nigrelli and others. Returned to AMNH and had an hour's talk with Mayo(?r) on taxonomic subjects. He is most interesting. Continued with library work at AMNH from 4 to 5. A good day.

Went to The King and I in the evening.

Notes:

Awramj

The name might be Mayo, but the last letter looks more like an "r"

Page Edit History:
  • Awramj 09/29/2012 12:24 AM
  • BPOC 09/17/2012 05:38 PM

37

Wednesday, February 6, 1952

Arrived at the NY Public Library at 9:15 and worked there until 4:15 except for time out for lunch. Cleared up a lot of items and had a successful day. Went to Gigi in the evening.

Page Edit History:
  • Awramj 09/29/2012 12:27 AM
  • BPOC 09/17/2012 05:38 PM

38

Thursday, February 7, 1952

Went to a meeting of utility presidents sponsored by the Edison Electric Institute 9:30 to 4:15. Very interesting and business-like.

Went to Caesar and Cleopatra in the evening.

Page Edit History:
  • Awramj 09/29/2012 12:29 AM
  • BPOC 09/17/2012 05:38 PM

39

Friday, February 8, 1952

Went to a meeting of the EEI Research Committee from 9:00 to 1:00 and then had lunch with the bunch. Packed and caught the Century to Chicago at 6:00.

Page Edit History:
  • Awramj 09/29/2012 12:31 AM

Saturday, February 9, 1952

Tuesday, February 12, 1952

Went to Los Angeles on the 3:15 train. Talked on Rattlesnakes and Man at the Hancock Auditorium from 8 to 9:10 with plenty of questions afterwards. A good crowd and they seemed interested. Saw Garth, Durham, and Fox.

  • Awramj 09/29/2012 12:37 AM

Friday, February 22, 1952

  • Awramj 09/29/2012 12:45 AM

54

Saturday, February 23, 1952

Spent most of the day on income tax computations, and finish them.

Went to a Zoo director's meeting at noon. Mrs. Benchley agreed to publish the South American rattler paper, preferably separate from the Mexican.

At the meeting, Milton Wegeforth brought up the matter of the rattler book stating that action that was to have been taken at the January meeting was not done, as Mrs. B was to have looked up former action in the minutes, which had not been done.

Page Edit History:
  • Awramj 09/29/2012 12:48 AM
  • BPOC 09/17/2012 05:38 PM

55

Sunday, February 24, 1952

Spent a large part of today on checking the Mexican taxonomic paper proof. Found plenty more mistake. Also went over the South American paper to incorporate the items picked up in the east.

Out to lunch with Ed and the family.

Page Edit History:
  • Awramj 09/29/2012 12:51 AM
  • BPOC 09/17/2012 05:38 PM

Wednesday, February 27, 1952

Went to Los Angeles on the 11:45 train.

First attended an insurance company board meeting; then went to the LA Public Library and worked from 4:15 to 6:15. Cleared up the Bernal Diaz del Castillo item.

  • Awramj 09/29/2012 12:53 AM

Wednesday, March 26, 1952

Friday, March 28, 1952

The Lark 1 3/4 hr. late this morning. Drove down from LA arriving at 1:45. Catching up this evening.

Page Edit History:
  • Awramj 10/04/2012 11:18 PM
  • BPOC 09/17/2012 05:38 PM

89

Saturday, March 29, 1952

I had lately, while traveling, reread Redi, Charas, Fontana et al and made suitable notes. Today, except for the zoo meeting, I spent the time improving the biting mechanism section by incorporating suitable historical references. Also shortened it somewhat by cutting down the parts of the fang descriptions taken from the Occ. Papers. Worked hard on this and made good progress.

This noon at a meeting of the Zoo director's they took formal action looking to the publication of the book. Set aside $7000 at present in the publication fund (including my $3000) and agreed to put $6,500 per year for next 2 years in the fund to make the total $20,000.

Page Edit History:
  • Awramj 10/04/2012 11:22 PM
  • BPOC 09/17/2012 05:38 PM

134

This morning at 7:30, started for Claremont and Yosemite with gg.

1 M. lateralis DOR L at Alberhill, Riverside Co., saved

At noon made a talk on books and book collecting to the girls at Scripp's College. Also looked through the library. Then went on to Mojave, via San Bernandino, where we put up at the Mojave Auto Court -- a good one.

Started out on the evening drive at 7:45 PDST. still plenty light. Cool and windy. Went to a point 10 mi. S. of Kramer Junction and back. Was cold and windy. 65° F at Mojave when we returned at 10:20.

1 Scute M DOR 3 mi. S. of Kramer Junct. was only snake seen.
Miles evening drive 92. Time 2:35.
